📌 Project Overview
This project is an end-to-end Credit Card Analytics Solution developed using Power BI and PostgreSQL.
It analyzes customer transactions, revenue trends, and behavior through interactive dashboards.
The project includes:
📊 Transaction Report Dashboard
👥 Customer Analysis Dashboard
🎯 Objectives
Analyze revenue and transaction trends
Perform customer segmentation
Build interactive dashboards for insights
Enable data-driven decision making
🔗 Data Source & Integration
Connected PostgreSQL database with Power BI
Imported CSV data into PostgreSQL
Performed data transformation using Power Query
Created relationships between tables
🗄️ Database Setup (PostgreSQL)
📌 Transaction Table
SQL
CREATE TABLE cc_detail (
    col1 TEXT, col2 TEXT, col3 TEXT, col4 TEXT, col5 TEXT,
    col6 TEXT, col7 TEXT, col8 TEXT, col9 TEXT,
    col10 TEXT, col11 TEXT, col12 TEXT, col13 TEXT,
    col14 TEXT, col15 TEXT, col16 TEXT, col17 TEXT, col18 TEXT
);
SQL
COPY cc_detail
FROM 'C:/credit_card.csv'
DELIMITER ','
CSV HEADER;
SQL
ALTER TABLE cc_detail RENAME COLUMN col1 TO client_num;
ALTER TABLE cc_detail RENAME COLUMN col2 TO card_category;
ALTER TABLE cc_detail RENAME COLUMN col3 TO annual_fees;
ALTER TABLE cc_detail RENAME COLUMN col4 TO activation_30_days;
ALTER TABLE cc_detail RENAME COLUMN col5 TO customer_age;
ALTER TABLE cc_detail RENAME COLUMN col6 TO week_start_date;
ALTER TABLE cc_detail RENAME COLUMN col7 TO week;
ALTER TABLE cc_detail RENAME COLUMN col8 TO quarter;
ALTER TABLE cc_detail RENAME COLUMN col9 TO year;
ALTER TABLE cc_detail RENAME COLUMN col10 TO current_debt;
ALTER TABLE cc_detail RENAME COLUMN col11 TO credit_limit;
ALTER TABLE cc_detail RENAME COLUMN col12 TO total_revolving_bal;
ALTER TABLE cc_detail RENAME COLUMN col13 TO total_trans_amt;
📌 Customer Table
SQL
CREATE TABLE cust_detail (
    client_num TEXT,
    customer_age INT,
    gender TEXT,
    dependent_count INT,
    education_level TEXT,
    marital_status TEXT,
    state_cd TEXT,
    zipcode INT,
    car_owner TEXT,
    house_owner TEXT,
    personal_loan TEXT,
    contact TEXT,
    customer_job TEXT,
    income INT,
    cust_satisfaction_score INT
);
SQL
COPY cust_detail
FROM 'C:/Users/RAJU/OneDrive/Desktop/power bi/customer.csv'
DELIMITER ','
CSV HEADER;
🔗 Data Modeling
Connected cc_detail and cust_detail using client_num
Built relationships in Power BI for combined analysis
📊 DAX Calculations
🔹 Age Group
Dax
AgeGroup =
SWITCH(
    TRUE(),
    'public cust_detail'[customer_age] < 30, "20-30",
    'public cust_detail'[customer_age] >= 30 && 'public cust_detail'[customer_age] < 40, "30-40",
    'public cust_detail'[customer_age] >= 40 && 'public cust_detail'[customer_age] < 50, "40-50",
    'public cust_detail'[customer_age] >= 50 && 'public cust_detail'[customer_age] < 60, "50-60",
    'public cust_detail'[customer_age] >= 60, "60+",
    "Unknown"
)
🔹 Income Group
Dax
IncomeGroup =
SWITCH(
    TRUE(),
    'public cust_detail'[income] < 35000, "Low",
    'public cust_detail'[income] >= 35000 && 'public cust_detail'[income] < 70000, "Medium",
    'public cust_detail'[income] >= 70000, "High",
    "Unknown"
)
🔹 Revenue
Dax
Revenue =
'public cc_detail'[annual_fees] +
'public cc_detail'[total_trans_amt] +
'public cc_detail'[interest_earned]
🔹 Week Number
Dax
week_num2 = WEEKNUM('public cc_detail'[week_start_date])
🔹 Current Week Revenue
Dax
Current_week_Revenue =
CALCULATE(
    SUM('public cc_detail'[Revenue]),
    FILTER(
        ALL('public cc_detail'),
        'public cc_detail'[week_num2] =
        MAX('public cc_detail'[week_num2])
    )
)
🔹 Previous Week Revenue
Dax
Previous_week_Revenue =
CALCULATE(
    SUM('public cc_detail'[Revenue]),
    FILTER(
        ALL('public cc_detail'),
        'public cc_detail'[week_num2] =
        MAX('public cc_detail'[week_num2]) - 1
    )
)
🔹 Week-over-Week Growth
Dax
wow_revenue =
DIVIDE(
    [Current_week_Revenue] - [Previous_week_Revenue],
    [Previous_week_Revenue]
)
